Effects of enamel-bonding, type of restoration, patient age and operator on the 
longevity of an anterior composite resin.

Smales RJ(1).

Author information:
(1)University of Adelaide, South Australia.

This study examined the survival of an anterior composite resin placed with or 
without enamel acid-etching using a low viscosity enamel bonding resin, for 
periods of approximately 16 years. The 950 conventional composite resin 
restorations were placed by numerous students and dentists for patients 
attending a dental hospital. Restorative failures were assessed using the life 
