Arumugam K(1), Urquhart R.

Author information:
(1)Department of Obstetrics and Gynaecology, University of Aberdeen, Scotland.

The cumulative pregnancy rates in 17 infertile patients with minimal or mild 
endometriosis who underwent laparoscopic electrocoagulation were compared with 
those of 20 similar patients who underwent only diagnostic laparoscopy. A 
life-table method of analysis was used. No significant differences in pregnancy 
rates was evident at either 6 months (p greater than 0.5) or 12 months (p 
