49. Am J Hum Genet. 1991 Oct;49(4):735-45.

Covariate-dependent age-at-onset distributions for Huntington disease.

Krawczak M(1), Bockel B, Sandkuijl L, Thies U, Fenton I, Harper PS.

Author information:
(1)Institute of Human Genetics, Göttingen, Germany.

A combined logistic regression and life-table analysis is presented on 
age-at-onset data for Huntington disease. Covariates included in the analysis 
were sex of the at-risk individual, parental age at onset, and sex of 
transmitting parent. Parental age at onset and parental sex were found to be 
significant covariates for age at onset in the offspring, and the appropriate 
logistic regression functions are calculated by maximum likelihood methods. 
These regression functions permit a more precise evaluation of carrier risks and 
likelihoods than hitherto was possible by simple computational means. We further 
introduce a novel method to account for sibship correlations in the significance 
assessment, using log-likelihood differences between different models.

